24/10/2010
BRATISLAVA, Slovakia -- The EU's enlargement commissioner, Stefan Fuele, believes there is a good chance EU foreign ministers will decide to forward Serbia's EU membership application to the Commission when they meet on Monday (October 25th). Speaking on Friday in Bratislava, he expressed optimism about the prospects.
Fuele was in the Slovakian capital to attend a meeting of foreign ministers from the Visegrad Group -- Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland and Slovakia -- and the Western Balkans. Serbian Foreign Minister Vuk Jeremic, who took part in the meeting, said the Visegrad Group has voiced its firm support for the EU prospects of Western Balkan countries. (FoNet, Blic, RTS - 22/10/10)
